<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="179" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,153,827]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,584,611]" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Discussion.</emphasis>
Despite of usual general appearance this is a somewhat peculiar species within the European 
<taxonomicName authority="(Idiocera)" authorityName="Dale" authorityYear="1842" baseAuthorityName="Idiocera" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Idiocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Idiocera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">Idiocera (Idiocera)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having four separate gonostyli of which the second one is rather stout and sickle-shaped. In contrast, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lackschewitz" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[255,484,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Idiocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexanderiana" subGenus="Idiocera">
<emphasis box="[255,484,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="179">I. (I.) alexanderiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Alexander" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[540,734,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Idiocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laterospina" subGenus="Idiocera">
